The paper deals with probabilistic inference over relational structures, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a probabilistic modeling language and a generic Metropolis-Hastings MCMC algorithm suggests a focus on probabilistic reasoning and inference, which is also relevant to the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions a citation matching task, which suggests a potential application in databases (cs.DB). Finally, the use of partial descriptions of possible worlds and context-specific Bayes nets suggests a potential application in social and information networks (cs.SI).
